When it comes to service, value, atmosphere, professional/friendly staff, large, well equipped rooms, you will not find a better hotel.	This is a small, refined European style hotel with a quiet, reserved atmosphere decorated in muted colors and historical prints.	The hotel bar and restaurant is lovely with excellent food and cocktails (and pricey)--dark panelled wood, velvet drapes and a fireplace.	Rooms are a bit frayed at the seams - carpet, upholstery, furniture all a bit dated and ready for an upgrade, but the location is superb, and overall experience very satisfactory.	The blousy Olde Englishe decor is fussy and overbearing, and not even well executed - the woodwork is cheaply done and the hallways narrow and dimly lit.